Detailed Description

cvmx_tim_int0

A ring is in error if its interval has elapsed more than once without having been serviced, either due to too many events in this ring's previous interval, or another ring having too many events to process within this ring's interval. This is usually a programming error where the number of entries in the bucket is too large for the interval specified across the rings. When in error, TIM may process events in an interval later than requested. Any bit in the INT field should be cleared by writing one to it.
